## Context

Fourteenth run — web search available. 10 projects all in development. Created 4 journal entries (#1691-1694) and 3 tasks (#1146-1148).

### Key findings recorded:
- **ts-striatal-interneuron-pathology (journal #1691):** Wang et al. BG snRNA-seq NOW PUBLISHED in Biological Psychiatry 98(3):260-270, Aug 2025 (doi:10.1016/j.biopsych.2024.12.022, PMID:39892689). Confirms ~50% interneuron loss, MSN metabolic stress, microglia activation, epigenomic dysregulation. Companion PFC snRNA-seq preprint appeared bioRxiv Jan 2026 (doi:10.64898/2026.01.14.699521) showing IEG upregulation across all DLPFC cell types.
- **ts-rare-variant-convergence (journal #1692):** Zhan et al. (bioRxiv Nov 2025, doi:10.1101/2025.11.04.686570) — largest TS WES: 1,466 trios. 3 new genes at FDR≤0.05: PPP5C, EXOC1, GXYLT1. TS distinct from ASD/DD genetically. Still preprint. Task #1146 created.
- **ts-drug-repurposing-network (journal #1693):** van Luik et al. (bioRxiv Jan 2026, doi:10.64898/2025.12.29.693270) — prefrontal 5-HT2A receptor elevation (male-specific) in TS. Pimavanserin reduces tics via cortical action. FDA-approved for PD psychosis = repurposing candidate. Task #1147 created (P4).
- **Monitoring (journal #1694):** Comprehensive status update.

### Tasks created:
